author: @KylePiira
text: In Keras there are two methods that can be used to load batches directly from disk: - model.train_on_batch(x, y) - trains a individual batch on some x and y data  - model.fit_generator(generator) - works the same as the fit method but takes a generator that outputs pairs x, y. This is the same method that model.fit() uses internally.

author: @Krish-ly3ps
text: @sentdex, in your pygame tutorials, you mentioned that eyes can only see up to 30 fps. That is false. Most humans can see between 200-280 frames per second. The monitor you have has a fps limit, but the eyes can easily differentiate between 30 and even 60 fps, let alone something like 240.
